In most cases, water is contaminated either by sewage, pollution or from flooding. Experts say the recent flooding caused by cyclones Idai and Kenneth in Mozambique and Zimbabwe has wreaked havoc in the countries with regards to water safety. For more on this, Kgomotso Mophulane spoke to Proffesor Tobias Barnard, Director of the University of Johannesburg's Water and Health Research Centre... --ChannelAfrica--